============================================================================
 Reference build log  —  MyCloud_Gen1_Debian_Stretch_Reflash
============================================================================
 A real capture of one clean run of
     build/build-stretch-stage1.sh  ..  stage4-package.sh
 (Debian 9 Stretch armhf, cross-built under qemu-arm-static on a WSL2 host,
 2026-07-09). Committed so you can compare your own run against a known-good
 one. Wall-clock ~12 min; nearly all of it is apt/gcc running under emulation.

 Only two mechanical edits were applied to this capture — nothing else:
   * absolute host build paths replaced with $REPO (the repo root, exactly as
     every build script computes it)
   * the apt "(Reading database ... 5% 10% ...)" progress spam collapsed to
     one line each

 BENIGN WARNINGS you WILL see, and can ignore (all expected on this box):
   * insserv: fopen(/etc/insserv.conf): No such file or directory
       — appears ONCE, early; insserv's own package drops that file moments
         later and every later insserv run is clean.
   * insserv: warning: script 'devfs'/'initmarker' missing LSB tags
       — expected: those two are inittab sysinit actions, deliberately NOT
         insserv-managed, so they carry no LSB header.
   * invoke-rc.d: could not determine current runlevel
       — expected: there is no running init inside the build chroot, so
         services register but cannot be (re)started here.
   * update-rc.d: warning: start and stop actions are no longer supported;
     falling back to defaults
       — harmless; "defaults" is exactly what we want.
   * debconf: delaying package configuration, since apt-utils is not installed
       — expected in a minbase rootfs.

 What a CORRECT run proves (verified structurally — no hardware flash; clio is
 in production). See docs/04-building-the-rootfs.md for the full write-up:
   * stage 2 step [1b] prints "dev-nodes: 37 device nodes present" (the static
     /dev nodes MUST be baked before /dev is bind-mounted — see docs/04)
   * libsystemd.so.0 stub, wsdd2, and recycle.so all LOAD-aligned 0x10000
   * the udev *package* is never installed; libsystemd0 is apt-mark held
   * tools/alignment-scan.sh comes back misaligned_libs=0
============================================================================


